(42, 19, 3, 42, 12, 25, 25, 'little of stature', 'Connection of Stature and Thought', 'This connection highlights the theme of stature in both passages. In Luke 19:3, the physical limitation of stature is emphasized, while Luke 12:25 reflects on the futility of trying to change one''s stature through thought.', 'theme', 0.272, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 23, 9, 10, 10, 'sycomore', 'Connection of Sycomore References', 'This connection highlights the mention of ''sycomores'' in both passages. In Luke, the sycomore tree serves as a means for visibility, while in Isaiah, the cutting down of sycomores signifies a desire for transformation and rebuilding.', 'keyword', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 42, 5, 19, 19, 'to see him', 'Seeking Jesus in Unconventional Ways', 'This connection highlights the theme of individuals going to great lengths to see Jesus. In both passages, characters take unconventional actions—climbing a tree and accessing a rooftop—to overcome obstacles in their pursuit of Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 13, 27, 28, 28, 'sycomore tree', 'Connection of Sycomore Trees', 'Both passages emphasize sycomore trees, linking them in a thematic way. The mention of sycomore trees in both contexts highlights their significance in the biblical narrative.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 11, 10, 27, 27, 'sycomore tree', 'Connection of Sycomore Trees', 'This connection highlights the significance of sycomore trees in both passages. In Luke, the sycomore tree serves as a vantage point for seeing Jesus, while in 1 Kings, sycomore trees symbolize abundance in Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 30, 7, 14, 14, 'sycomore tree', 'Sycomore Tree Connection', 'This connection highlights the mention of the sycomore tree in both passages. In Luke, the sycomore tree serves as a vantage point for seeing Jesus, while in Amos, it relates to the gathering of sycomore fruit.', 'keyword', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 4, 19, 78, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Sycomore Trees', 'This connection highlights the mention of ''sycomore trees'' in both passages. In Luke, the sycomore tree serves as a means for observation, while in Psalms, it is associated with destruction, suggesting a thematic link between visibility and vulnerability.', 'keyword', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
